getErrorResponse

public Response getErrorResponse()
Description copied from class: Request
Derived classes must overload this method to return a new response of the appropriate type. This is a convenience method for creating basic error responses so that we don't have to concern ourselves with the exact type of request - we just want to fill in some error information and fire it back.

Specified by:
getErrorResponse in class Request
Returns:
A response with its response type set to ERROR.
